            <abstract id="ref3" label="Abstract">Howard Goddard (1911-1997) dedicated much of his life to working as a union activist, from organizing in the early 1930s to a lifelong career with the International Union of Mine, Mill and Smelter Workers (IUMMSW). Goddard joined the International Brigades to fight against Franco in Spain in 1937 and returned in 1938 with the rank of Captain. This collection contains ephemera from the Spanish Civil War and correspondence between Goddard and various veterans and veteran organizations.</abstract>
            <origination label="creator">
                <persname source="local">Goddard, Howard, 1911-1997</persname>
            </origination>
        </did>
        <custodhist id="ref4">
